org.ensor.robots.motors

Interface ICurrentMeasurable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IMotor, IMotorWithEncoder

    public interface ICurrentMeasurable
    This interface models an object which has electrical characteristics of voltage drop and current draw. It is assumed that this component has a linear power dissipation characteristic.
    Author:
    jona

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getCurrentDraw()
      This method returns the current draw (in Amps) for the component.
      double getVoltage()
      This method returns the voltage drop across this component's input.
